text: **** NOTE: LEAVE BBL IN CLEAN RINSE IF THICKNESS CHECKS NEEDED *****
DIP SAMPLES PER BELOW
CHECK BLACK ADHESION AND APPEARANCE CLOSELY.
POST DIP:
1. ***** BLACKEN IMMEDIATELY AFTER PLATE *****
2. TURN IN POST DIP STATIONS @ PLATING RPM
3. NITRIC DIP 10 SEC. TO ACTIVATE - RINSE
4. CAUSTIC PRE-DIP 45-90 SEC. RINSE IN BOTH ALKALINE RINSES & CHOMATED RINSE
A. WASHERS AND NUTS WILL NEED LONGER DIP TIMES THAN BOLTS.  PARTS SHOULD
HAVE UNIFORM DULL GRAY APPEARANCE AFTER PRE-DIP.
B. PARTS MUST BE RINSED VERY WELL, TO MINIMIZE DRAG-IN OF HIGH PH
PRE-DIP SOLUTION.  THIS WILL HELP AVOID CONTAMINATION OF THE
BLACKENING SOLUTION.
5. BLACK DIP: 2-8 MIN. AS NEEDED TO ACHIEVE BLACK APPEARANCE, THEN RINSE
NOTE: A. FLAT PARTS WILL NEED LONGER DIP TIMES
B. YOU SHOULD NOT SEE ANY IRIDESCENCE WHEN PARTS ARE BLACK ENOUGH
C. **** IF PARTS TAKE LONGER THAN 8 MIN. TO BLACKEN - CALL LAB ****
6. HYPRO 250 SEAL 45 SEC. - DRAIN WELL AFTER SEAL 30 SEC. TURNING SLOW
NOTE: DO NOT RINSE AFTER SEAL
DRYING PROCEDURE:
1. OKAY TO DRY PARTS IN HARSHAW BASKETS
2. SPIN OFF PARTS WITH NO HEAT 15 SEC. - TO REMOVE EXCESS SEAL.
NOTE:  SEAL WILL PUDDLE IF NOT SPUN OFF FIRST.
3. DRY WELL WITH HEAT.
DRYING TEMP = 180 DEG.
DRYING TIME = 10 MINS. MINIMUM
4. DO NOT OVER-DRY PARTS AS THIS WILL ALSO CAUSE EXCESSIVE SCRATCHING
INSPECTION PROCEDURE:
APPEAR: 1. PARTS MUST BE BLACK IN COLOR (NOT BROWN, GREEN, ETC.)
NOTE: SOME VERY SLIGHT IRRIDESCENCE IS ACCEPTABLE
2. PARTS SHOULD HAVE SOME SHINE TO FINISH, SHOULD NOT BE DULL
3. PARTS SHOULD NOT BE EXCESSIVELY SCRATCHY
4. MAKE SURE PARTS ARE TOTALLY DRY, LOOK FOR SEAL PUDDLING
5. SPECIAL APPEARANCE TEST:
A. RUB SMOOTH AREAS OF PART AND MAKE SURE BLACK DOES NOT COME
OFF.  IF THE BLACK RUBS OFF, THIS USUALLY INDICATES AN
ACTIVATION ISSUE BEFORE THE BLACK DIP.
